Description: How do you want it all to end? [This determines how you win: although you can always just retire in London, for a draw.]
LevelDescriptionText: 1|Complete the King's Cradle Foundation's commission~2|Retire to a life of luxury~3|Bring peace to the Unterzee~4|Found your own private kingdom~5|Sail East, beyond the Zee~6|Liberate the secret of immortality
Name: Objective: Ambition

Description: No one was born a zee-captain.
LevelDescriptionText: 1|A Past Wreathed in Shadows~2|A Chimneysweep~3|An Invalid~4|A Soldier~5|A Circus Performer~6|A Gardener~7|An Heir
ChangeDescriptionText: 1|For now, you are a mystery~3|You were a Sickly Invalid. Now, you're a zee-captain~2|You were a Lowly Chimneysweep. Now, you're a zee-captain~4|You were a Weary Soldier. Now, you're a zee-captain~5|You were a Circus Performer. Now, you're a zee-captain~6|You were a Cautious Gardener. Now, you're a zee-captain~7|You were a Slovenly Heir. Now, you're a zee-captain
Name: Memoirs: Your Past

Description: How do they speak to you?
LevelDescriptionText: 1|Madam~2|Sir~3|Citizen~4|my lord~5|my lady~6|Captain~7|you magnificent b_stard~8|Mistress~9|my dude~100|(mumble)
Name: Addressed As

Description: Let's go!
LevelDescriptionText: 0|The race is on!~10|The race is off.
ChangeDescriptionText: 0|The race is on!~10|The race is off.
Name: A Day at the Races

Description: Buzz buzz.
LevelDescriptionText: 0|The Swarm hungers~10|The Swarm has been destroyed
ChangeDescriptionText: 0|The Swarm hungers~10|The Swarm has been destroyed
Name: State of the Swarm

Description: There is a yearning.
Name: End Paren: Familiarity

Description: There is a yearning.
Name: End Paren: A House of Questions

Description: The mines are primarily for coal, but it's the side products that everyone cares about.
LevelDescriptionText: 0|You are uninvolved with the mines at Dis.~1|Take the Miner to Dis.~2|The mines of Dis are shut.~4|The mines of Dis are closed permanently.~3|The mines are open!
ChangeDescriptionText: 0|You are uninvolved with the mines at Dis.~1|Take the Miner to Dis.~2|The mines of Dis are shut.~4|The mines of Dis are closed permanently.~3|The mines are open!
Name: Objective: Jade Mining

Description: Jade is good, just not too much. [Speak to the Shogunate politely or send them a violent message.]
Name: Jade Mining: Shogunate Interference

Description: Accidents in the dark? Or something more sinister? [Investigate the disappearances or help to cover them up.]
Name: Jade Mining: Missing Miners

Description: No one can work without their coffee. [Go to Umwelt Isles to figure out why the shipment hasn't arrived, or deliver it yourself.]
Name: Jade Mining: Late Shipments

Description: The heart is a heedless hunter. [You are engaged in a discreet liaison with one of your Officers.]
LevelDescriptionText: 1|Perplexed Helmsman~2|Unlicensed Therapist~8|Cladery Heir~4|Campaigner~3|Mechanic~7|The Daughter~6|Magician~5|Nacreous Survivor
ChangeDescriptionText: 2|You have begun an affair with the Unlicensed Therapist~1|You have begun an affair with the Perplexed Helmsman~3|You have begun an affair with the Tireless Mechanic~4|You have begun an affair with the Campaigner~5|You have begun an affair with the Nacreous Survivor~6|You have begun an affair with the Magician~7|You have begun an affair with Maybe's Daughter~8|You have begun an affair with the Cladery Heir
Name: Romance: an Affair with...

Description: The Shogunate's power is growing.
LevelDescriptionText: 1|Kaifuku~5|Sairai~7|Kagayakashī~2|Yūbō~3|Jūyōna~4|Jūdai~6|Tohōmonai
Name: Supremacy: The Shogunate

Description: We sleep. We hunger. We rise.
LevelDescriptionText: 5|Napping~7|AWAKENED~4|Slumbering~3|Dozing~1|Sleeping~6|Dreaming~2|Snoozing
Name: Supremacy: Ozao Remnants

Description: Such quiet, clever little things.
LevelDescriptionText: 5|Pollinating~7|Infested~4|Budding~3|Growing~1|Seeding~6|Spreading~2|Germinating
Name: Supremacy: The Umwelt Dynasty

Description: She's watching you, from wherever she is.
ChangeDescriptionText: 1|You now have the Gods of the Zee: Shade's Attention.
Name: The Gods of the Zee: Shade's Attention

Description: A curse lies on you: the curse of the great Wyrm of the depths.
LevelDescriptionText: 1|Shade's curse lies on you
ChangeDescriptionText: 1|Shade's curse lies on you
Name: The Gods of the Zee: Shade's Curse

Description: There are powers.
ChangeDescriptionText: 1|You know something of the three gods of the zee.
Name: The Gods of the Zee: Sleet, Shade and Silver

Description: He's watching you, perhaps from closer than you think.
LevelDescriptionText: 1|You now have the Gods of the Zee: Silver's Attention
ChangeDescriptionText: 1|You now have the Gods of the Zee: Silver's Attention.
Name: The Gods of the Zee: Silver's Attention

Description: You carry a curse: the curse of the great Wyrm of wealth and fortune.
LevelDescriptionText: 1|Silver's Curse lies on you
ChangeDescriptionText: 1|Silver's Curse lies on you.
Name: The Gods of the Zee: Silver's Curse

Description: A mighty hunger knows you.
LevelDescriptionText: 1|You now have the Gods of the Zee: Sleet's Attention
ChangeDescriptionText: 1|You now have the Gods of the Zee: Sleet's Attention.
Name: The Gods of the Zee: Sleet's Attention

Description: A curse lies on you: the curse of the great Wyrm of weather and hunger.
LevelDescriptionText: 1|Sleet's curse lies on you
ChangeDescriptionText: 1|Sleet's curse lies on you
Name: The Gods of the Zee: Sleet's Curse

Description: The things you'll do for your employer...
LevelDescriptionText: 100|Visit the Fathomking~4|Bring a Hunting-Trophy to London~200|Fulfil the Fathomking's Requests~54|Seek Kingeater's Castle, in the far south-east~53|Seek a parcel with your name in Nuncio, somewhere in the south of the zee~56|Seek Visage, somewhere in the south of the zee~52|Seek the Bone Men in the Chelonate, in the east of the zee~300|Fathomking's Requests Fulfilled~55|Seek Horizon's Aspect, in the North~400|A Message for the Chapel of Lights~3|Bring a Failed Novel from the Gallery of Sentences to London~5|Bring Romantic Literature to London~2|Bring a sample of Red Honey to London~6|Bring a Port Report from the Umwelt Isles to London~7|Bring Strategic Information to London
ChangeDescriptionText: 4|Bring a Hunting-Trophy to London~5|Bring Romantic Literature to London~6|Bring a Port Report from the Umwelt Isles to London~53|Seek a parcel with your name in Nuncio, somewhere in the south of the zee~54|Seek Kingeater's Castle, in the far south-east~55|Seek Horizon's Aspect, in the North~56|Seek Visage, somewhere in the south of the zee~100|Visit the Fathomking~200|Fulfil the Fathomking's Requests~300|You have fulfilled the Fathomking's Requests~400|You have a Message for the Chapel of Lights~500|Bring your father back to London~3|Bring a Failed Novel from the Gallery of Sentences to London~52|Seek the Bone Men in the Chelonate, in the east of the zee~2|Bring a sample of Red Honey to London~7|Bring Strategic Information to London
Name: The Commission: A Faulty Start

Description: The best listeners have the best stories.
Name: The Gallery of Sentences: Floors Unlocked

Description: Higher. Higher!
Name: The Gallery of Sentences: Floors Explored

Description: Stony shards protrude from the most uncomfortable of places.
Name: Menaces: Cragwarts

Description: Thick, yellow tears refuse to stop flowing.
Name: Menaces: Weeping Sickness

Description: Something at the back of your throat refuses to dislodge.
Name: Menaces: Cancroid Cough

Description: You are haunted by ghosts of the past.
Name: Menaces: Aghemnia

Description: Indentations along your features mark you as one of the stricken.
Name: Menaces: Pitpox

Description: Hurry on, we don't have all day!
ChangeDescriptionText: 0|It is time to return to your ship.~1|Moving along...
Name: Bestiary: The Zoo Path Shuffle

Description: No circuses.
LevelDescriptionText: 1|You sided with the Piercing Inspector~2|Bring a package from Hermitage to the Piercing Inspector
ChangeDescriptionText: 1|You sided with the Piercing Inspector~2|Bring a package from Hermitage to the Piercing Inspector
Name: Bestiary: Dealings with the Piercing Inspector

Description: For the last time, it's a zoo.
LevelDescriptionText: 1|You sided with the Nefarious Zookeeper~2|Bring a package from Hermitage to the Nefarious Zookeeper
ChangeDescriptionText: 1|You sided with the Nefarious Zookeeper~2|Bring a package from Hermitage to the Nefarious Zookeeper
Name: Bestiary: Dealings with the Nefarious Zookeeper

Description: Your network needs you.
Name: Networks: An Opportunity - Château-Dessous

Description: You have spies in Château-Dessous.
Name: Networks: Château-Dessous

Description: Travel deep enough, and you'll find something interesting.
LevelDescriptionText: 0|You've returned from the World of Light!
ChangeDescriptionText: 10|Something looming...~20|A feeling of being watched...~30|Destroyed structures...~40|Piercing cold...~50|Somewhere, a moan...~60|Invisible architecture...~70|Oily secretions...~80|Unending light...~90|Frigid landscapes...~1|A distant roar...~100|Something that doesn't belong...
Name: Another Day: The World of Light

Description: It can't be closed off to everyone. [Someone in End Paren may know more.]
Name: The Machine: A Way In

Description: Woe betide those who treat the Machine poorly.
Name: The Machine: Machinist's Terror

Description: Treat the Machine kindly, and it will be kind to you.
Name: The Machine: Trust of the Machine

Description: You've fed the Machine.
Name: The Machine: Maintenance (A)

Description: You've pleased the Machine.
Name: The Machine: Maintenance (B)

Description: You've aided the Machine.
Name: The Machine: Maintenance (C)

Description: You've cleaned the Machine.
Name: The Machine: Maintenance (D)

Description: You've read from the Machine.
Name: The Machine: Maintenance (E)

Description: But to what?
Name: The Machine: The Key

Description: A tradition old as time.
LevelDescriptionText: 1|You've brought children to London.~100|Bring children to Ztargon's Remains or release them in London.~200|You brought children to the Ozao.~201|You released children in London.
ChangeDescriptionText: 1|You've brought children to London.~100|Bring children to Ztargon's Remains or release them in London.~200|You brought children to the Ozao.~201|You released children in London.
Name: Objective: The Oldest Profession

Description: Making a baby isn't what it used to be. [Go to The Human Factory to pick up a child.]
ChangeDescriptionText: 1|Your sweetheart is ready to have a child.
Name: Romance: a Notable Occasion

Description: What flavour this is you cannot imagine. Perhaps that's the point.
Name: Hermitage: Judgment's Egg

Description: Can hermit-slugs eat this? You hope the Face knows what it's doing.
Name: Hermitage: Salt

Description: You have options, though not many. What dares grow in the Neath?
Name: Hermitage: Something Grown

Description: How sweet need the honey be?
Name: Hermitage: Sweetest Honey

Description: Good for the soul, or so they claim.
Name: Hermitage: Soup

Description: One day, the zee. One day.
LevelDescriptionText: 1|Seek Swarmspice in Culicida.~2|Listen.~3|Fulfil Who Weeps' requests.~4|You took the Invasive Ozao with you.~5|You killed the Invasive Ozao.
ChangeDescriptionText: 1|Seek Swarmspice in Culicida.~2|Listen.~3|Fulfil Who Weeps' requests.~4|You took the Invasive Ozao with you.~5|You killed the Invasive Ozao.
Name: Hermitage: Who Weeps' Hunger

Description: Playtime never ends.
LevelDescriptionText: 1|You are known to the Fae.
ChangeDescriptionText: 1|You are known to the Fae.
Name: Faeble: The Fae

Description: Unless you're rather young for a zee-captain, these are unlikely to grow back.
Name: Missing Teeth

Description: You won't be very well off without these.
Name: Missing Eyes

Description: How refreshing!
Name: Freshly Bathed

Description: This'll come back to bite you, no doubt.
Name: Intoxication

Description: Couldn't you just stay here forever?
Name: The Palace's Pull

Description: Addictive, isn't it?
ChangeDescriptionText: 1|The game is on!
Name: A Game of Chance

Description: This will allow you to descend into the beast's flesh.
Name: Krakenchute Permit

Description: A Crooked Vendor is selling Parabola-Linen at bargain prices.
LevelDescriptionText: 1|Parabola-Linen is for sale.~30|Sold out!
ChangeDescriptionText: 1|Buy another?~30|Sold out!
Name: Favours: Selling Scraps

Description: The... sun?
LevelDescriptionText: 1|You know a little too much.
ChangeDescriptionText: 1|You know a little too much.
Name: Sunshade Redoubt: Twilight Hours

LevelDescriptionText: 0|Dyi Ztar~1|Port Jasper~2|Shitakyoto~3|Dyi Ztar~4|Orchid Island
ChangeDescriptionText: 1|A new force rules Dyi Ztar
Name: Dyi Ztar's Name

Description: Are you sure you know what you're doing?
Name: Rath Ruin: That Sinking Feeling

Description: Your name is known to those trapped by the Resort.
Name: Zyme Resort: Contacts

Description: They're willing to give you a wide berth. For safety, of course.
Name: Zyme Resort: Security

Description: An unlikely friendship blossoms.
Name: Zyme Resort: The Paranoid Mutterer

Description: Just how long was she here?
Name: Zyme Resort: The Scorned Translator

Description: The stirrings of revolution.
Name: Zyme Resort: Last Request

Description: A full mouth has loose lips.
Name: Zyme Resort: Grub's Up

Description: Worth the risk?
Name: Zyme Resort: Fresh Air

Description: Even without light, your actions have been observed.
Name: Zyme Resort: Sunlight

Description: Does she watch, even now?
Name: Zyme Resort: The Bone Warden

Description: Uh-oh.
Name: Zyme Resort: In Chaos

Description: You've welcomed a stranger aboard your ship. This may lead to complications.
LevelDescriptionText: 1|Consequences wait.
ChangeDescriptionText: 1|Welcome aboard!~0|A certain matter has become clear.
Name: A Clean Bill Of Health

Description: Where's the treasure?
LevelDescriptionText: 2|the Western beach~3|where children splash and play~4|the Northern hills~5|the rolling green~6|the Eastern homestead~7|the heart's hearth~8|the base of the statue~9|the feet of the king
ChangeDescriptionText: 1|A clue!
Name: Henson's Landing: Clue 1

Description: Where's the treasure?
LevelDescriptionText: 0|~2|at the collapsed cave~3|at the adventure untold~4|at the lighthouse~5|at the place which wards against disaster~6|at the rock which looks like a face~7|at Henson's visage
ChangeDescriptionText: 1|A clue!
Name: Henson's Landing: Clue 2a

Description: Where's the treasure?
LevelDescriptionText: 0|~2|at the pale mushroom~3|at a pillar of ivory~4|at the blemmigan nest~5|where monsters sing~6|at the signpost~7|where X marks the spot
ChangeDescriptionText: 1|A clue!
Name: Henson's Landing: Clue 2b

Description: Where's the treasure?
LevelDescriptionText: 0|~2|at Henson's grave~3|where our Father rests~4|at the outhouse~5|where water is hung to dry~6|at the garden~7|where toil is rewarded
ChangeDescriptionText: 1|A clue!
Name: Henson's Landing: Clue 2c

Description: Where's the treasure?
LevelDescriptionText: 0|~2|at the three stones~3|at the gray haiku~4|at the crossroads~5|at the meeting of the ways~6|at the fallen stalactite~7|at Sleet's spear
ChangeDescriptionText: 1|A clue!
Name: Henson's Landing: Clue 2d

Description: Where's the treasure?
ChangeDescriptionText: 1|A clue!
Name: Henson's Landing: Clue 3

Description: Where's the treasure?
LevelDescriptionText: 2|North~3|towards the point of His emergence~4|West~5|towards London~6|East~7|towards the Mistress's Lair~8|South~9|towards the world's edge
ChangeDescriptionText: 1|A clue!
Name: Henson's Landing: Clue 4

Description: Here's the treasure!
Name: Henson's Landing: Solution 1

Description: Here's the treasure!
Name: Henson's Landing: Solution 2a

Name: Henson's Landing: Solution 2c

Name: Henson's Landing: Solution 3

Name: Henson's Landing: Solution 4

Description: Here's the treasure!
Name: Henson's Landing: Solution

Description: How long has this been going on?
Name: Henson's Landing: The Gravesite

Description: That song is still stuck in your head.
Name: Henson's Landing: Treasures Abound

Description: This is legitimate, yes?
Name: Aditta: A Fiery Enterprise

Description: What won't you see?
Name: Seaglass: An Incomparable View

Description: Ruin has come to our family...
Name: Clayborne Place: The Manor's Mysteries

Description: Oh, what a tangled web we weave!
Name: The Old Magnanery: Strands of Fate

Description: How does your garden grow?
Name: Hypatia: Vines and Victuals

Description: How far is too far?
Name: Trojan's Rook: A Leap Too Far

Description: Even small gods can grant big boons.
Name: Trojan's Rook: Mr. Feathers' Trust

Description: Heavy lies the crown. Heavier still hangs the sword.
Name: Objective: King for a Day

Description: To there ye shall return.
ChangeDescriptionText: 1|You came to Dresden via Esau's Ladder.~2|You came to Guernica via the Zeppelin.~3|You came to Wyrmsmouth via dirigible.~4|You came to Wyrmsmouth via the Zeppelin.
Name: From Whence Came Ye?

Description: You are far from home.
LevelDescriptionText: 0|Dresden~1|Guernica~10|Vienna
ChangeDescriptionText: 0|Avernus: grey rock and blue water.~1|Naples: crowded streets and the sea's horizon~10|Vienna: revolution in the air
Name: The Cruelty of Sunlight

Description: Probably insignificant.
Name: A Man in Black

Description: Probably insignificant.
Name: A Man in White

Description: One more couldn't hurt.
Name: Menaces: Addiction

Description: How well are the Gardeners holding out?
Name: Oishigetta: Might

Description: Tread carefully.
ChangeDescriptionText: 1|You are welcome to dock at Oishigetta.~2|You are the hero of Oishigetta!~3|A certain matter has been concluded.
Name: Oishigetta: Acknowledged

Description: Trust is a fragile thing.
Name: Oishigetta: Suspicion

Description: Your presence will only be tolerated for so long.
Name: Time in Oishigetta

Description: You've made Shogunate friends.
Name: Favours: A Pewter Horsehead

Description: Novelty only lasts so long.
Name: Sales of Swarmspice

Description: Who lurks in this heart of stone?
ChangeDescriptionText: 1|Someone waits in the dark.
Name: The Dark Gates

Description: Was this a good idea?
Name: Favours: Freed Zamurai

Description: You've welcomed a stranger aboard your ship. This may lead to complications.
LevelDescriptionText: 1|Consequences wait.
ChangeDescriptionText: 1|Welcome aboard!~0|A certain matter has become clear.
Name: A Pirate Aboard

Description: Tale as old as time.
Name: Faeble: Pirate's Gold

Description: Profundity is mundane.
ChangeDescriptionText: 1|Wisdom flows as a blade cuts.
Name: The Sword Saint

Description: Try what thou might, do as thou wilt, the Shogun cares not.
Name: Kantai: Shogun's Indifference

Description: What horrible fate befell this ship and her crew?
Name: Aboard the Repressor

Description: Stony shards protrude from the most uncomfortable of places.
Name: Menaces: Watched

Description: What can be said of this place that would not alter itself a moment later?
LevelDescriptionText: 1|waterlogged wood~2|metal sheets~3|crunching glass shards~4|moors with the consistency of orange zest~5|ancient ashes
ChangeDescriptionText: 1|Lightning-fast, Mekhane changes once again...
Name: Mekhane: Constant Shifting 1

Description: What can be said of this place that would not alter itself a moment later?
LevelDescriptionText: 1|aflame~2|a lush blue~3|frozen and captured in ice during their full bloom~4|molting~5|waving madly
ChangeDescriptionText: 1|Lightning-fast, Mekhane changes once again...
Name: Mekhane: Constant Shifting 2

Description: What can be said of this place that would not alter itself a moment later?
LevelDescriptionText: 1|a ztardog~2|some kind of marsupial~3|a bag of fruits~4|an incongruent serpent~5|a curious panther
ChangeDescriptionText: 1|Lightning-fast, Mekhane changes once again...
Name: Mekhane: Constant Shifting 3

Description: What can be said of this place that would not alter itself a moment later?
LevelDescriptionText: 1|a gangrenous big toe~2|a child’s toy~3|an unclear bomb~4|an entire flock of pigeons~5|a triskelion talisman
ChangeDescriptionText: 1|Lightning-fast, Mekhane changes once again...
Name: Mekhane: Constant Shifting 4

Description: What can be said of this place that would not alter itself a moment later?
LevelDescriptionText: 1|hot chicken soup~2|rotting flesh~3|pepper~4|burning trash~5|roses
ChangeDescriptionText: 1|Lightning-fast, Mekhane changes once again...
Name: Mekhane: Constant Shifting 5

Description: Great and wonderful things lie just out of our reach.
Name: Kirai Komainu: A Fanciful Dream

Description: Beyond the pale lies an endless emptiness.
Name: Kirai Komainu: A Dismal Dream

Description: What fun and excitement lie ahead?
Name: Henson's Landing: A Call to Adventure

Description: Limited-time offer! Don't miss it!
Name: Henson's Landing: One Time Only

Description: Maybe there's some truth to the myth after all.
Name: Henson's Landing: Another Treasure

Description: The plan's in your hands.
Name: Henson's Landing: The Scallywag's Stash

Description: What lies below this idyllic place?
Name: Henson's Landing: The Sealed Cave

LevelDescriptionText: 1|The light has touched you lightly~50|The light compels~100|When you close your eyes, you see the light. There is something in the North~200|Your time is over. Rise and give yourself to the Sun
ChangeDescriptionText: 1|The light: it's pretty.~10|The light: it's like nothing else in the Neath.~20|The light is a wonder.~30|The light is a glory.~40|The light fascinates.~50|The light compels.~60|The light draws you, constantly.~70|The light is a secret electricity in your blood.~80|The memory of the light is always with you.~90|The memory of the light is always with you. Go on. Open a box.~100|When you close your eyes, you see the light.~110|When you close your eyes, you see shapes in the light. Flowers?~120|Whenever you close your eyes, you see the shining flowers writhe. Something is wrong.~130|Dancing flowers fill your vision. This isn’t how it’s supposed to be.~140|Dancing flowers fill your vision. They’re the same as the mists to the South.~150|The South is a vast nothingness. The Sun is everything. Why do you see one in the other?~160|An intense wrongness occupies your blurred vision.~170|Behind your eyes is a flurry of burning petals.~180|An understanding dawns. So close, so close.~190|An understanding dawns. Oh God. Oh God.~200|That’s not a Sun.
Name: Menaces: Yearning, Burning

Description: What waits above?
Name: Wyrmsmouth: Unnatural Sights

Description: Coal, dug from zee-cliffs or the mines of Dis. [If you run out of fuel, you will drift helplessly.]
Name: Fuel

Description: A sinister little squatting image... but its eyes are pleading.
Name: Watchful Curio

Description: A hundred dreams in every barrel.
Name: Firkin of Prisoner's Honey

Description: Oh, how it glitters.
Name: Neath Jade

Description: At some point, it stops being desecration and starts being science.
Name: Fossil

Description: Spare screws, hex keys, flasks of oil... everything a machine needs to stay healthy.
Name: A Gift for the Machine

Description: Far from dogs, but friendly enough if kept fed. [Ammunition for Ozao weapons.]
Name: Ztardog

Description: Containers within containers. What do they contain? Best not speculate.
Name: An Assortment of Uncomfortably Large Eggs

Description: The Château's finest. A gift worthy of kings.
Name: Cask of Château-Dessous 1866

Description: Well-trained and entirely loyal. You hope.
Name: Networks: A Diplomatic Agent

Description: It illuminates.
Name: Pearl of Light

Description: She knows the ins and outs of the Machine.
Name: Nervous Machinist

Description: It has a coppery smell to it. Probably copper. [Deliver this to The Human Factory.]
Name: A Barrel of "Parts"

Description: You never know when you might need one of these!
Name: A Heavy Wrench

Description: Don't dawdle. They grow up so fast.
Name: Children

Description: Considered a delicacy. Zailors who've lost eyes use these as replacements.
Name: Jellied Eyeball

Description: Creation. Destruction. Everything in the middle some muddied combination of the two.
Name: Botanist's Bible

Description: Dried, ground insects, sure to add a certain flavour to your food.
Name: Swarmspice

Description: The crew are nervous about keeping this aboard. You should be, too.
Name: Ereshkigal

Description: Never mind the contents. The fact that you need this is far more worrying.
Name: Ill-Advised Preventative Medicine

Description: The rocking of the boat is not having the soothing effect that it should. Bring a mop.
Name: Sickly Sailor

Description: Everything is a disgrace, all of it.
Name: Faded Provocateur

Description: Already pieces fall away like dandruff across the deck.
Name: Crumbling Noman

Description: "What is property?" she asks, and seems annoyed when you define the term for her.
Name: Oblivious Anarchist

Description: Leaving in style.
Name: Scented Deathmasque

Description: A single swipe can change history.
Name: Ceremonial Sword

Description: You've done London proud.
Name: Medal of Valor

Description: It clinks pleadingly.
Name: Jarred Memento

Description: The Emperor is pleased.
Name: Medal of Honour

Description: Let's see what we can see, shall we?
Name: Colourproof Goggles

Description: The exterior is only half the story.
Name: Silvered Self-Portrait

Description: Has it been worth it, truly?
Name: Medal of War

Description: And now it never will be.
Name: Unfinished Painting

Description: The swirling shapes reveal everything and nothing.
Name: Telekailedoscope

Description: It's all starting to come together.
Name: Zee Thesis

Description: But you can bear it, can't you?
Name: Burning Ring

Description: You're still not over it.
Name: Rare Postage

Description: It commands no respect, but tradition is tradition.
Name: Ringmaster's Hat

Description: But we all know why you really did it, don't we?
Name: Medal of Philanthropy

Description: It burns and burns but is never extinguished. What a thought, to know that traces of the Gods can be captured in a simple jar.
Name: Wyrmsbreath

Description: Remember, you paid for this.
Name: Esau's Ladder Advance Pass

Description: A pack a day keeps the doctors away.
Name: Box of Cigars

Description: Crude but effective.
Name: Gardeners' Axes

Description: Chess doesn’t drive people mad, it keeps mad people sane.
Name: Chess Pieces

Description: Keep it secret. Keep it safe.
Name: Immaterial Dagger

Description: This will grant you access to Shogunate trade.
Name: Trade Permit

Description: Such treasures are only found under an equally blue sky.
Name: A Casket of Sapphires

Description: Green as the zee and twice as deadly.
Name: A Casket of Emeralds

Description: Rarer than good advice.

Name: A Port Report: The Human Factory

Description: You've seen where the means of production lie.
Name: Surveyed: The Human Factory

Description: Crawling with anger. Thirsting for revenge.

Description: Tick tock.
Name: A Port Report: Sunshade Redoubt

Name: Surveyed: Wyrmsmouth

Description: "Omnia mors perimit et nulli miseretur"
Name: Nergal's Roar

Description: Granted, his features are a little on the unusual side.
Name: Hairy Marksman

Description: Dashingly handsome, but you can't charm the zee.
Name: Perplexed Helmsman

Description: When nothing is worth cooking, nothing gets cooked.
Name: Fastidious Gourmet

Description: She's not much for splints or bandages, but it's amazing what a kindly word can do.
Name: Unlicensed Therapist

Description: She's rather taken with you, and perhaps too keen for her own good.
Name: Impressionable Student

Description: It prefers to shimmy rather than walk, and cannot be cajoled into a run.
Name: Prancing Pony

Description: It hails from another world. Is it another world? Or an unseen part of this one?
Name: Angelic Moth

Description: Its artifial eyes pick up the slightest glint. It enjoys snatching zailors' hats.
Name: Mechanical Magpie

Description: The stink of Ozaean flesh lies upon it. Its cold eyes observe your actions dispassionately.
AvailableAt: Sometimes lurking on the docks of London.
Name: Ozaean Doll

Description: From a distance it looks like a stone. Up close, it looks like a stone with a smile.
Name: Personable Tortoise

Description: This adorable little friend loves to sing and dance for your crew, and even helps out around the ship! What a star!
Name: Lovable Little Buddy

Description: When she thinks you're not listening, she curses to herself in the tongues of far-off lands.
Name: Scorned Translator

Description: He's got sunshine on a Neathy day.
Name: Sunny Surfacer

Description: An aura of dark mystery suffuses him, but his piercing gaze discourages your own.
Name: Grim Quartermaster

Description: She darts about in dim corners of the engine room, appearing to rather wish that she was anywhere else.
Name: Frightened Apprentice

Description: Her mood has much improved. Her visibility has not.
Name: Outgoing Apprentice

Description: Time among the Ozao has changed his features... and perhaps more.
Name: Weary Ambassador

Description: She seems always on the cusp of violence, even away from the guns.
Name: Pale Widow

Description: It's easier to see once the veil is lifted.
Name: Blushing Widow

Description: What use is a legend that nobody's heard of?
Name: Shrunken Hero

Description: Thankfully, her food is far less foul than her attitude.
Name: Noxious Butcher

Description: Whom does he really serve?
Name: Shadowed Servant

Description: The zee inspires fear in some and fervor in others.
Name: Gregarious Occultist

Description: What was once a blind faith has opened its eyes.
Name: Wide-Eyed Occultist

Description: It's bravery to commit to science in a land bereft of reason.
Name: Dubious Naturalist

Description: Madness can, itself, be an answer.
Name: Loathing Naturalist

Description: One who has seen the majesty of the world and found it wanting.
Name: Invigorated Naturalist

Description: Prize within reach, he now turns to you.
Name: Hungering Zee-Hunter

Description: Rich and respected - but a hunter is never satisfied.
Name: Well-Fed Zee-Hunter

Description: All the zee's a stage.
Name: Incomparable Actress

Description: Though seemingly docile, there's an ancient anger in its eyes.
Name: Intrusive Ozao

Description: A jovial nature is undercut by steely nerves and precise movements.
Name: Rambunctious Ronin
